<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<I c="Tutorial" i="tutorial" m="tutorials.tutorial" n="tutorial_EP21_ProjectGold_NobleCareer" s="489306">
  <T n="category">488441<!--TutorialCategory: tutorial_Category_EP21_ProjectGold--></T>
  <T n="name">0x360CCD54<!--String: "Noble Active Career"--></T>
  <L n="slides">
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP21\UI\Tutorial\EP21_Lessons_NobleCareer1.png">2f7d0004:00000000:287f78842059de45</T>
      <T n="text">0xD4434E8D<!--String: "The <b><font color='#199C2C'>Noble Career</font></b> is a new active career where your Sim assumes the responsibility of ruling a Kingdom and ensuring the prosperity of their subjects whilst navigating the drama of Noble Court. \n\nYou can join the Noble Career in different ways, try selecting a high-ranking Noble and <b><font color='#199C2C'>Request a Knighthood</font></b> under the Friendly social category. You can also find the book; <b><font color='#199C2C'>The Duchess Diaries: A History of Nobility</font></b> in any bookshelf, then use it to <b><font color='#199C2C'>Research Noble Legacy</font></b>. Or place a <b><font color='#199C2C'>throne object</font></b> from Build/Buy and select <b><font color='#199C2C'>Join Noble Career</font></b>. "--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP21\UI\Tutorial\EP21_Lessons_NobleCareer2.png">2f7d0004:00000000:287f78842059de46</T>
      <T n="text">0x36731645<!--String: "Noble Sims can structure their workday around their lives; each day, a new set of <b><font color='#199C2C'>Noble Duties</font></b> will appear, which can be completed to <b><font color='#199C2C'>earn Career Progression</font></b>. Noble Duties can vary depending on your Sim's career rank with some busy days filled with Grand Balls and Noble Speeches whilst others will be much quieter giving Noble Sims a chance to relax\n\nNoble Sims can also go on a <b><font color='#199C2C'>Noble Venture</font></b> once a day. Sims will leave and return after a few hours with a career performance increase and Noble Favor. To go on a Noble Venture, select your Noble Sim, then the Noble Ventures category or use a throne object and select the Noble Ventures category. "--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP21\UI\Tutorial\EP21_Lessons_NobleCareer_Promotion.png">2f7d0004:00000000:21cc3fac0dc2102a</T>
      <T n="text">0x20E06343<!--String: "To climb the ranks your Sims must have excellent career performance and have completed all their <b><font color='#199C2C'>Promotion Tasks</font></b>. When your Sim is ready to claim their new rank and title they can use <b><font color='#199C2C'>Noble Promotion</font></b> on the Throne object or, from Level 3 in the career, they can either <b><font color='#199C2C'>Receive Promotion through Coronation Speech</font></b> or <b><font color='#199C2C'>Receive Promotion through Coronation Ceremony</font></b>.\n\nIf your Sims would prefer to skip the ceremony, <b><font color='#199C2C'>automatic career progression</font></b> can be enabled in the Pack Settings menu. If enabled Sims will receive an automatic promotion at 7am if they qualify."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP21\UI\Tutorial\EP21_Lessons_NobleCareer_Promotion2.png">2f7d0004:00000000:30205b5b60c1776c</T>
      <T n="text">0x31E1141D<!--String: "<b><font color='#199C2C'>Only 1 Sim per world can reach the top rank of the career</font></b> and rule. For your Sim to reach this coveted position they must remove any existing top ranked Noble before they can claim it for themselves. This Noble Rival can be seen in your Sim's Career Panel.\n\nDealing with <b><font color='#199C2C'>Noble Rivals</font></b> can be done in a more righteous way by having your Sim or the Rival's Dynasty Head encourage them to abdicate. Your Sim could also Duel using their Swordsmanship skill to claim the title. If that route is too honorable, your Sims can pursue more nefarious means by pressuring, seducing, or extorting their rival. Rivalries also end if the Rival dies or is demoted."--></T>
    </U>
  </L>
  <L n="tags">
    <E>Lesson_EP21_ProjectGold_NobleCareer</E>
  </L>
